Source: bob
Section: science
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Biometrics Group <biometric@idiap.ch>
Build-Depends: @cdbs@, cmake, python-dev, python-support, python-numpy, liblapack-dev, libatlas-base-dev, libblitz0-dev, ffmpeg, libavcodec-dev, libswscale-dev, libboost-all-dev, libavformat-dev, graphviz, libmatio-dev, libmagick++-dev, libhdf5-serial-dev, libqt4-dev, libfftw3-dev, libcv-dev, libhighgui-dev, libsvm-dev, doxygen, python-sphinx, dvipng
# Build-Recommends: libgoogle-perftools-dev
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/idiap/bob
Homepage: http://idiap.github.com/bob

Package: bob
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${python:Depends}, python, python-argparse, python-scipy, python-matplotlib, python-sqlalchemy
Recommends: ipython, hdf5-tools, h5utils
Suggests: libhdf5-doc
Description: A toolbox for Biometrics, Machine Learning and Signal Processing
 Bob is a signal-processing and machine learning toolbox for Biometrics developed at the Idiap Research Institute, in Switzerland. The toolbox is written in a mix of Python and C++ and is designed to be both efficient and to reduce development time.

